Acknowledgement of Public-Domain-Derived Files (CC0-1.0)

Separately from the carve-out above, a set of files derive from Philippe Ozil's
streaming-monitor project (https://github.com/pozil/streaming-monitor), which is
dedicated to the public domain under CC0-1.0. CC0-1.0 waives all copyright and
related rights and imposes no attribution requirement, so these files are NOT
carved out above: they are relicensed under the Business Source License 1.1
alongside the rest of the Licensed Work, which CC0-1.0 expressly permits.

They are listed here purely as an acknowledgement, not a licence obligation. We
credit Philippe Ozil because it is the right thing to do, even though CC0-1.0
does not require it. His original tool is free on the AppExchange (listing
a0N3A00000FYEEWUA5). The full CC0-1.0 text is shipped at LICENSES/CC0-1.0.txt.

Adapted from streaming-monitor, Copyright (c) Philippe Ozil (rights waived
under CC0-1.0):

  LWC components (11, under force-app/main/default/lwc/): streamingActions,
    streamingEventFilters, streamingEvents, streamingEventsHeader,
    streamingMonitor, streamingSidebar, streamingSubscriptions,
    streamingTimeline, streamingUsageFilters, streamingUsageMetrics,
    utilityStreaming.

  Apex classes (under force-app/main/default/classes/): CTRL_EventMonitor.cls
    and CTRL_EventMonitor_TEST.cls in full, and SEL_EntityDefinition.cls in
    part (the streaming channel-discovery query methods only).

